        "title": "feat(durable): harden worker execution and recovery",
        "body": "## Stack / Dependency Note\n\nThis is Batch D in the OpenClaw-X durable-core stack.\n\nDepends on:\n- PR1 / #97507: durable coordination RFC\n- PR2 / #97508: opt-in durable coordination kernel\n- Batch A / #97666: restart and schema lifecycle proof\n- Batch B / #97667: intake, branch routes, Task Flow projection\n- Batch C / #97668: Workboard durable projection visibility\n\nGitHub currently shows batch PRs against `main`, so this PR may include earlier dependency commits in the commit list. The intended unique review diff is the execution hardening layer after Batch C.\n\nInternal plan coverage: PR5 + PR6 + PR10.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Adds a feature-flagged durable worker loop for safe registered handlers.\n- Adds stale workflow lease protection and guarded recovery behavior.\n- Adds side-effect retry policy guards so unsafe or unknown effects are not replayed blindly.\n\n## Why\n\nPR2 proves the durable coordination kernel as an inspectable control plane. Batch D starts hardening the runtime authority path without claiming exactly-once external side effects.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- No Postgres backend.\n- No external workflow engine adapter.\n- No broad channel delivery rewrite.\n- No Workboard UI changes in this batch.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `npm test -- src/durable/worker.test.ts src/durable/recovery.test.ts src/durable/executor.test.ts src/durable/routes.test.ts src/durable/sqlite-store.test.ts src/durable/store-factory.test.ts src/durable/human-signal.test.ts src/durable/taskflow-bridge.test.ts src/durable/intake.test.ts src/durable/fan-in.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.browser.test.ts`\n- `npm run ui:build`",
